 {"id":"bd-27bm","title":"Implement session-level events (before/after flush/commit/rollback)","description":"## Description

Add session-level event hooks.

## Python Behavior

```python
@event.listens_for(Session, 'before_flush')
def before_flush(session, flush_context, instances):
    for obj in session.new:
        validate(obj)

@event.listens_for(Session, 'after_commit')
def after_commit(session):
    clear_cache()
```

## Rust Implementation

```rust
pub trait SessionEvents {
    fn before_flush(&mut self, new: &[&dyn Model], dirty: &[&dyn Model], deleted: &[&dyn Model]) 
        -> Result<(), Error> { Ok(()) }
    fn after_flush(&mut self) -> Result<(), Error> { Ok(()) }
    fn before_commit(&mut self) -> Result<(), Error> { Ok(()) }
    fn after_commit(&mut self) -> Result<(), Error> { Ok(()) }
    fn after_rollback(&mut self) -> Result<(), Error> { Ok(()) }
}
```

Or closure-based:
```rust
session.on_before_commit(|| {
    info\!("About to commit");
    Ok(())
});
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] before_flush sees pending changes
- [ ] after_flush called after successful flush
- [ ] before_commit called before COMMIT
- [ ] after_commit called after COMMIT
- [ ] after_rollback called after ROLLBACK
- [ ] Events can abort (return Err)

