 {"id":"bd-27un","title":"Implement sqlmodel_update()","description":"## Description

Update model instance from dict or another model.

## Python Behavior

```python
user.sqlmodel_update({'name': 'New Name'})
user.sqlmodel_update(other_user)
user.sqlmodel_update(partial_update, update={'extra': 'value'})
```

## Rust Implementation

```rust
pub trait SqlModelUpdate {
    fn sqlmodel_update(&mut self, source: impl Into<UpdateSource>) -> Result<(), Error>;
}

pub enum UpdateSource {
    Dict(HashMap<String, Value>),
    Model(Box<dyn Any>),
}

impl<M: Model> SqlModelUpdate for M {
    fn sqlmodel_update(&mut self, source: impl Into<UpdateSource>) -> Result<(), Error> {
        match source.into() {
            UpdateSource::Dict(dict) => {
                for (key, value) in dict {
                    self.set_field(&key, value)?;
                }
            }
            UpdateSource::Model(other) => {
                // Copy non-None fields
            }
        }
        Ok(())
    }
}
```

